1.11	Confession_(album)	Confession (album)	Confession is the second album released by Ill Ni√±o. The album debuted at #37 in the Billboard Top 200 with first week sales of 27,863. It has been their most successful album to date, selling nearly 500,000 copies in the United States. The album features several elements and influences of alternative metal. It was the last album to feature Marc Rizzo, who left during recording to join Soulfly, and also the first to feature Ahrue Luster, formerly of Machine Head/	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/3c/Illni%C3%B1oconfession.jpg/220px-Illni%C3%B1oconfession.jpg
